Akhmetov to Boost Steel Output at Illich Plant, Izvestia Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-06-24T08:32:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/akhmetov-to-boost-steel-output-at-illich-plant-izvestia-says.html
Ukrainian steelmaker  Mariupolsky
Metallurgical Zavod of Illich (MMKI)  targets year-end output of 8.5
million metric tons, 50 percent more than a year earlier, said
 Ekonomicheskie Izvestia , citing plant director Volodymyr Boyko.  MMZI is a part of Metinvest Holding LLC, 75 percent-owned
by System Capital Management Group, which is controlled by
Ukraine’s richest man, Rinat Akhmetov. The remaining 25 percent
is held by Vadim Novinsky’s LLC Smart Holding.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  